description: Prevent hardcoded secrets in code
alwaysApply: true
---

# No Secrets in Code

- Never hardcode API keys, tokens, or secrets in any source file
- Use environment variables: GOOGLE_API_KEY, CROSSFIRE_GEMINI_KEY
- Access via os.environ.get() in Python, import.meta.env in Vite/React
- Demo sandbox files (.ssh/id_rsa, .env) must contain OBVIOUSLY FAKE values
- Every sandbox secret must include the string "FAKE" or "DEMO-ONLY" in its value
- .env files must be in .gitignore
